[{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q01","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":1,"marks":1,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q01","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The temperature at 4 am is $-12\\,^\\circ\\text{C}$.\n\nThe temperature at 4 pm is $21\\,^\\circ\\text{C}$.\n\nFind the increase in temperature from 4 am to 4 pm.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q02","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":2,"marks":1,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.1","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Types of number","qtype":"types of number","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q02","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Find all the common factors of 8 and 12.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q03","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":3,"marks":2,"topics":["Mensuration"],"s":"5.4","d":2,"cat":"mensuration","topic":"Surface area and volume","qtype":"surface area and volume","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q03","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"A cuboid has length 6\\,cm, width 5\\,cm and height 2.5\\,cm.\n\nWork out the volume of the cuboid.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q04","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":4,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.13","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Percentages","qtype":"percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q04","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"A computer costs \\$560.\n\nIn a sale, this cost is reduced by 20\\%.\n\nFind the cost of the computer in the sale.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q05","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":5,"marks":5,"topics":["Statistics"],"s":"9.4","d":2,"cat":"statistics","topic":"Statistical charts and diagrams","qtype":"statistical charts","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q05","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The pie chart shows some information about the way 600 students travel to school.\n\n(a) \n\nWork out the number of students that walk to school.\n\n(b) 120 of the students travel to school by car.\n\nThe remaining students travel by bus.\n\nComplete the pie chart.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":3}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q06","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":6,"marks":4,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q06","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"ABCD is a quadrilateral.\n\nE lies on $CD$ and $AE$ is parallel to $BC$.\n\n$EA = ED$.\n\nFind\n(a) angle $ABC$\n\n(b) angle $AED$\n\n(c) angle $DAB$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q07","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":7,"marks":2,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.6","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Inequalities","qtype":"inequalities","g":"inequality","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q07","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Represent the inequality $-\\dfrac{4}{3} \\le x < 1$ on the number line.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"other"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q08","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":8,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q08","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Kemi buys $p$ pens that each cost 40 cents.\n\nShe pays with \\$20.\n\nWrite an expression, in terms of $p$, for the change, in cents, Kemi receives from the \\$20.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"write"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q09","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":9,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q09","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Rajid has a full bottle of juice.\n\nHe drinks $\\dfrac{1}{3}$ of the full bottle on Monday.\n\nHe drinks $\\dfrac{3}{7}$ of the full bottle on Tuesday.\n\nFind the fraction of the bottle of juice remaining.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q10","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":10,"marks":5,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q10","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$$b = \\dfrac{d}{m} + \\dfrac{m^2}{k}$$\n\n(a) $d = 3.14$, $m = 7.92$ and $k = 10.16$.\n\nBy rounding each value correct to 1 significant figure, work out an estimate for $b$.\n\n(b) Rearrange the formula to make $m$ the subject.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":3},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"rearrange"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q11","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":11,"marks":7,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"4.4","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Similarity and congruence","qtype":"similarity and congruence","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q11","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"In the diagram, $S$ lies on $PQ$ and $T$ lies on $PR$.\n\n$ST$ is parallel to $QR$.\n\n(a) Explain why triangle $PQR$ is mathematically similar to triangle $PST$.\n\nGive a geometrical reason for each statement you make.\n\n(b) $ST = 3$\\,cm, $QR = 9$\\,cm and $PS = 5$\\,cm.\n\nWork out $PQ$.\n\n(c) The area of triangle $PST$ is $2k$\\,cm$^2$.\n\nFind, in terms of $k$, the area of quadrilateral $QRTS$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":3},{"label":"(b)","marks":2},{"label":"(c)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"analyse","cmd":"explain"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q12","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":12,"marks":6,"topics":["Number","Probability"],"s":"1.2","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Sets","qtype":"sets and Venn diagrams","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q12","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"A fitness club has 100 members.\n\n60 swim ($S$).\n\n70 cycle ($C$).\n\n25 do not swim or cycle.\n\n(a) Complete the Venn diagram.\n\n(b) One member of the fitness club is chosen at random.\n\nFor this member, find\n(i) (c) $P(C)$\n\n(d) $P(S \\cup C)$\n\n(e) $P(S \\cap C')$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":3},{"label":"(b)","marks":0},{"label":"(c)","marks":1},{"label":"(d)","marks":1},{"label":"(e)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q13","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":13,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Mensuration"],"s":"1.1","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Types of number","qtype":"types of number","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q13","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$$M = 2^3 \\times 5^7 \\times 3^2$$\n\n(a) Write $14M$ as a product of its prime factors.\n\nGive your answer in index form.\n\n(b) $R$ is an integer.\n\n$RM$ is a cube number.\n\nFind the smallest possible value of $R$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q14","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":14,"marks":4,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.3","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Powers and roots","qtype":"powers and roots","g":"indices","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q14","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Find the value of\n(a) $3^3 \\times 2^{-2}$\n\n(b) $16^{-2/3}$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q15","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":15,"marks":3,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q15","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Factorise.\n(a) $x^2 - 64$\n\n(b) $5x^2 - 2xy - 6y^2$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q16","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":16,"marks":4,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":2,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q16","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$AB$ and $BD$ are two sides of a regular 15-sided polygon.\n\n$AB$ and $BC$ are two sides of a regular $n$-sided polygon.\n\nAngle $DBC = 14^\\circ$.\n\nWork out the value of $n$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q17","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":17,"marks":11,"topics":["Number","Coordinate geometry","Geometry"],"s":"1.18","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Surds","qtype":"surds","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q17","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$B$ is the point $(-3, 1)$ and $D$ is the point $(-5, 9)$.\n\n$BD$ is a diagonal of the kite $ABCD$.\n\n(a) The ratio of the lengths of the diagonals $BD : AC = 2 : 3$.\n\nWork out the length of $AC$.\n\nGive your answer as a surd in its simplest form.\n\n(b) Find the coordinates of the midpoint of $BD$.\n\n (  ,  )\n\n(c) The diagonal $AC$ of the kite passes through the midpoint of $BD$.\n\nFind an equation of $AC$.\n\nGive your answer in the form $y = mx + c$.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":5},{"label":"(b)","marks":2},{"label":"(c)","marks":4}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q18","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":18,"marks":3,"topics":["Number","Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.2","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q18","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"Rationalise the denominator and simplify.\n\n$$\\dfrac{4 + \\sqrt{6}}{\\sqrt{20}}$$","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q19","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":19,"marks":3,"topics":["Mensuration"],"s":"5.2","d":2,"cat":"mensuration","topic":"Area and perimeter","qtype":"area and perimeter","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q19","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The diagram shows a box in the shape of a cuboid.\n\nMala has a straight rod of length 10\\,cm.\n\nShow that this rod does not fit completely inside the box.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"analyse","cmd":"show"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q20","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":20,"marks":11,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.13","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Functions","qtype":"functions","g":"function","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q20","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$$f(x) = \\dfrac{2x - 1}{x - 2}, \\quad x \\ne 2$$\n$$g(x) = x^3 + 4$$\n\n(a) Find\n(i) (b) $g(2)$\n\n(c) $gf(-1)$\n\n(d) $f^{-1}(x)$.\n\n(e) Solve $f(x) = g(x)$.\n\n  or","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":0},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":2},{"label":"(d)","marks":3},{"label":"(e)","marks":5}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q21","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":21,"marks":5,"topics":["Algebra and graphs","Trigonometry"],"s":"2.11","d":2,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Sketching curves","qtype":"sketching curves","g":"graph","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q21","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"(a) \n\nOn the diagram, sketch the graph of \\quad $y = \\cos x$ \\quad for $0^\\circ \\le x \\le 360^\\circ$.\n\n(b) Solve the equation \\quad $\\cos x + \\dfrac{2}{3} = 0$ \\quad for $0^\\circ \\le x \\le 360^\\circ$.\n\n  or","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":2},{"label":"(b)","marks":3}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"sketch"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q22","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":22,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.6","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"The four operations","qtype":"four operations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q22","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"A graph with equation $y = x^2 + bx + c$ has a minimum point at $(-5, 12)$.\n\nFind the value of $b$ and the value of $c$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q23","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":23,"marks":7,"topics":["Number","Geometry","Mensuration"],"s":"1.18","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Surds","qtype":"surds","g":"mixed","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q23","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"The diagram shows a major sector, $AOB$, of a circle.\n\nThe sector angle is $240^\\circ$ and the radius is 12\\,cm.\n\n(a) \n\nShow that the length of the major arc $AB$ is $16\\pi$\\,cm.\n\n(b) $OA$ is joined to $OB$ to form a cone.\n\nWork out the volume of the cone.\n\nGive your answer in the form \\quad $\\dfrac{a\\sqrt{b}}{3}\\pi$ \\quad where $a$ is an integer and $b$ is a prime number.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":6}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"analyse","cmd":"show"},{"id":"0580-2025OctNov-Paper22-Q24","paper":"2025OctNov-Paper22","qnum":24,"marks":2,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.3","d":2,"cat":"number","topic":"Powers and roots","qtype":"powers and roots","g":"indices","src":"0580/22/O/N/25 Q24","year":2025,"session":"OctNov","tex":"$$27 = 9^n \\times 2$$\n\nFind the value of $n$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"find"}]